 <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">⨆ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"As `⨆ i, f i = 0` when the domain of the real-valued function `f` is empty or unbounded above,\nit suffices to show that all values of `f` are nonnegative to show that `0 ≤ ⨆ i, f i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Archimedean.html#Real.iSup_nonneg","kind":"theorem","line":298,"name":"Real.iSup_nonneg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Data/Real/Archimedean.lean#L298-L300"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Archimedean.html#Real.sSup_nonneg\"><span class=\"name\">Real</span>.<span class=\"name\">sSup_nonneg</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hs</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">s</span>, <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤